					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; Yemenite square script, punctuated.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>194 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>420</height>
										<width>280</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>414</height>
										<width>218</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>194 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>20 quires of 10 leaves each, apart from the following: i8, xv9, xvii9, and xx8.</p>
									<p>The quires are signed with Hebrew letters on the first page and marked with catchwords on the last page. </p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="26" writtenLines="26">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Masorah magna in generally one line in the lower margin and occasionaly one line in the upper margin of the page.</p>
									<p>The beginning and the end of the Haftarot marked in the margin.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary> Yemenite square script, punctuated. <name type="person" role="scribe">Benayah [ben Sa&apos;adyah ben Zekharyah ben Margaz]</name>, for manuscripts of the same scribe see Or 2211, 2348, 2370, 2375. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Avraham ben Yosef</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, folio 193v. </p>
							<p>A birth record of the son of <name type="person" role="owner">Ibrahim ibn Yusuf</name>, inscribed on folio 193v, with a date of Adar <date calendar="Seleucid">1781</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1470</date>). </p>
							<p>A purchase note in Judeo-Arabic, folio 194v.</p>
						</additions>
